Sarkozy Ministers May Cut 10 Billion Euros in 2012, JDD Reports

-- B y   J a m e s   H e r t l i n g
-- 
2011-08-14T08:29:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-14/sarkozy-ministers-may-cut-10-billion-euros-in-2012-jdd-reports.html
French President  Nicolas Sarkozy ’s
government may target budget cuts of about 10 billion euros
($14.3 billion) in 2012 to reach deficit commitments,  Journal du
Dimanche  reported, without citing sources.  Measures may includes a tax increase on people earning more
than 900,000 euros and closing tax advantages for investors in
overseas French territories and real estate, the newspaper said.  Finance Minister  Francois Baroin  and Budget Minister
Valerie Pecresse met yesterday and they’ll make their initial
proposals to Sarkozy on Aug. 16, the report said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
James Hertling in Paris at 
 jhertling@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Craig Stirling at   cstirling1@bloomberg.net  